comment: Carroll (TOR) is in the lane for more than 3 seconds.
Mahinmi (IND) makes contact with DeRozan (TOR) while he is in the air and does not give him an opportunity to return to the floor.
RHH shows Biyombo (TOR) jumps vertically with George (IND), remains vertical, and absorbs the contact.
Hill (IND) grabs Valanciunas (TOR) as he attempts to secure the rebound.
Hill (IND) gives DeRozan (TOR) enough room to avoid the screen and he absorbs contact. DeRozan's contact with Hill (IND) is incidental.
Hill (IND) commits a take foul on Carroll (TOR).
Hill (IND) beats Carroll (TOR) to the spot (point of contact), giving him enough room to avoid the screen.
Hill (IND) commits a take foul on DeRozan (TOR).
Since Carroll (TOR) is moving to the side of Hill (IND) and Hill is not yet shooting, contact on this play is incidental and does not warrant a foul call.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined that Hill (IND) was fouled while attempting a three-point field goal and the ruling on the floor was overturned.
Allen (IND) commits a take foul on Valanciunas (TOR).
Since Carroll (TOR) is jumping past George (IND) and would have missed him had George not jumped forward into him, this is not a shooting foul.
